This paper deals with the security of machine learning models, specifically neural networks, and proposes a technique for detecting Trojan attacks. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also includes experiments on vision (cs.CV), speech (cs.SD), and natural language processing, indicating that it could potentially fit under those sub-categories as well.
